so I don't... What do we do?

90
00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:36.818
Well. normally.
I would report this to law enforcement.

91
00:04:36.901 --> 00:04:39.112
But given what he's been through. I won't.

92
00:04:40.822 --> 00:04:41.781
This time.

93
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:43.533
Thank you.

94
00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:46.077
But I am gonna have to suspend him
for two weeks.

95
00:04:46.536 --> 00:04:48.788
Maybe in that time.
he can get some counseling.

96
00:04:49.205 --> 00:04:52.834
And I know that Pastor Wayne has a group
for troubled teens down at the church.

97
00:04:52.917 --> 00:04:55.336
Well. I mean. he needs to be punished.
not tortured.

98
00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:59.924
It would be helpful to understand
where he got the pills.

99
00:05:01.676 --> 00:05:03.803
Tell her where you got
the pills from. Charlie.

100
00:05:03.886 --> 00:05:04.721
No.

101
00:05:07.223 --> 00:05:08.224
I... I can't.

102
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.891
Thank you for taking me on a ride along.

103
00:05:50.058 --> 00:05:52.977
It's so fascinating
to see how cops solve stuff.

104
00:05:53.186 --> 00:05:54.812
No problem.

105
00:05:55.563 --> 00:05:56.981
You know. it's nice to have company.

106
00:05:57.315 --> 00:06:00.193
What do you think it does
to a nine-year-old to find a bloody corpse

107
00:06:00.276 --> 00:06:01.444
by the side of the road?

108
00:06:01.944 --> 00:06:04.947
Um... I'm gonna go with
"scars her for life."

109
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:09.077
But maybe it becomes a defining moment

110
00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.789
