217
00:11:04.538 --> 00:11:08.626
♪ <i>At least I'll live as I believe ♪</i>

218
00:11:08.959 --> 00:11:13.005
<i>♪ No matter what they take from me</i> ♪

219
00:11:13.381 --> 00:11:18.552
<i>♪ They can't take away my dignity ♪</i>

220
00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:20.680
- He's so into it.
- So cute.

221
00:11:20.763 --> 00:11:21.764
<i>♪ Because the...</i> ♪

222
00:11:21.847 --> 00:11:22.890
What the hell?

223
00:11:23.265 --> 00:11:26.477
You're doing it wrong. you stupid idiots.

224
00:11:26.560 --> 00:11:28.270
They just messed up the whole show.

225
00:11:28.646 --> 00:11:30.481
I'm quitting this stupid choir!

226
00:11:30.898 --> 00:11:32.483
Oh. fuck me.

227
00:11:33.401 --> 00:11:36.821
Unfortunately.
this isn't an isolated incident.

228
00:11:38.531 --> 00:11:42.618
Henry is often quick to anger
when things aren't just so.

229
00:11:42.868 --> 00:11:46.372
Yeah. I just don't know
why nobody told me this was happening?

230
00:11:46.455 --> 00:11:50.042
Oh. I would've.
But Ted was my home contact.

231
00:11:50.543 --> 00:11:51.877
